  "text": "We recently undertook a research program that addresses health promotion toward young adults, specifically investigating mental health and risky health behaviors among college undergraduate students. As discussed above, mental health problems among this group are increasing [CITATION_1] and risky health behaviors, including overweight, smoking, drinking, and risky sex, are relatively high [CITATION_2] . Yet little research in the area of health promotion has been conducted among young adults due, in part, to difficulty of overcoming competing distractions of academic, social, and sporting activities, as well as the transient nature of this population's living situations [CITATION_3] .",
